# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldMage4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke early to Samayra still sleeping next to her."
    new "Sarah woke early to Samayra still sleeping next to her."

    old "Sarah felt guilty for having left Samayra to herself the day before."
    new "Sarah felt guilty for having left Samayra to herself the day before."

    old "Next to her, the former princess of Bagrad tossed and turned as if caught in a bad dream."
    new "Next to her, the former princess of Bagrad tossed and turned as if caught in a bad dream."

    old "Sarah reached out and softly touched her, shaking her awake."
    new "Sarah reached out and softly touched her, shaking her awake."

    old "Samayra's eyes shot open and her body jolted."
    new "Samayra's eyes shot open and her body jolted."

    old "Only when her eyes met Sarah's did she calm down."
    new "Only when her eyes met Sarah's did she calm down."

    old "Ooh...Sarah..."
    new "Ooh...Sarah..."

    old "It's ok. You were having a bad dream, I think."
    new "It's ok. You were having a bad dream, I think."

    old "I...I was..."
    new "I...I was..."

    old "Sarah didn't want to press her. She also could imagine, everything the girl had been through, what her nightmare had been about."
    new "Sarah didn't want to press her. She also could imagine, everything the girl had been through, what her nightmare had been about."

    old "I wanted to say sorry about yesterday. Leaving you alone like that, here in this strange house. I should have taken better care of you."
    new "I wanted to say sorry about yesterday. Leaving you alone like that, here in this strange house. I should have taken better care of you."

    old "It's ok. Sleeping here with you...it feels kind of safe."
    new "It's ok. Sleeping here with you...it feels kind of safe."

    old "Sarah was happy to hear she could offer Samayra at least that."
    new "Sarah was happy to hear she could offer Samayra at least that."

    old "I promise I'll make it up to you today. We'll go do something fun."
    new "I promise I'll make it up to you today. We'll go do something fun."

    old "Fun? Like what."
    new "Fun? Like what."

    old "Honestly...I don't know yet. But I'm sure we can figure it out, right?"
    new "Honestly...I don't know yet. But I'm sure we can figure it out, right?"

    old "The girl eagerly smiled and nodded."
    new "The girl eagerly smiled and nodded."

    old "Tell me, have you eaten anything since we came here?"
    new "Tell me, have you eaten anything since we came here?"

    old "Embarrassed, Samayra looked down and shook her head."
    new "Embarrassed, Samayra looked down and shook her head."

    old "Right, well get yourself something to eat and I'll see about if we can do something."
    new "Right, well get yourself something to eat and I'll see about if we can do something."

    old "Sarah made her way towards the door and left the room."
    new "Sarah made her way towards the door and left the room."

    old "Sarah woke to an empty bed, early the next morning."
    new "Sarah woke to an empty bed, early the next morning."

    old "The house had a silence that seemed overwhelming. The kind that pounded on the ears."
    new "The house had a silence that seemed overwhelming. The kind that pounded on the ears."

    old "Sarah sighed to herself, if only to break through the silence."
    new "Sarah sighed to herself, if only to break through the silence."

    old "Climbing out of the bed, she tried to think of what to do."
    new "Climbing out of the bed, she tried to think of what to do."

    old "There was the matter of the book, but it had only been a day and she had not heard anything from Razaphel."
    new "There was the matter of the book, but it had only been a day and she had not heard anything from Razaphel."

    old "Nor did she particularly care to dig much deeper for the moment."
    new "Nor did she particularly care to dig much deeper for the moment."

    old "Distraction. That was the real thing she needed right now."
    new "Distraction. That was the real thing she needed right now."

    old "Stepping out into the hallway, Sarah turned her head from side to side, orienting herself."
    new "Stepping out into the hallway, Sarah turned her head from side to side, orienting herself."

    old "It all still very much looked the same, but even that couldn't necessarily promise that nothing had changed."
    new "It all still very much looked the same, but even that couldn't necessarily promise that nothing had changed."

    old "Suddenly, the spirit manifested itself again."
    new "Suddenly, the spirit manifested itself again."

    old "Awake I see."
    new "Awake I see."

    old "You know, I think we're going to need to find you some friends, because I don't think it's healthy for you to spend all your free time with me."
    new "You know, I think we're going to need to find you some friends, because I don't think it's healthy for you to spend all your free time with me."

    old "The spirit hissed with laughter."
    new "The spirit hissed with laughter."

    old "You are great fun, Sarah."
    new "You are great fun, Sarah."

    old "Perhaps if you are bored of talking, there are other things we could do."
    new "Perhaps if you are bored of talking, there are other things we could do."

    old "How about you help me instead."
    new "How about you help me instead."

    old "Any particular matter?"
    new "Any particular matter?"

    old "Sarah looked across the hallway."
    new "Sarah looked across the hallway."

    old "Suppose..."
    new "Suppose..."

    old "She paused to consider."
    new "She paused to consider."

    old "Suppose someone wanted to do something...to just...relax?"
    new "Suppose someone wanted to do something...to just...relax?"

    old "The spirit swirled across the hall, its body bellowing like smoke from a chimney."
    new "The spirit swirled across the hall, its body bellowing like smoke from a chimney."

    old "Such simple desires."
    new "Such simple desires."

    old "I am only human, hard as that may be for you to remember. Everyone needs a break sometimes."
    new "I am only human, hard as that may be for you to remember. Everyone needs a break sometimes."

    old "The spirit twisted through the air a moment longer, before finally answering."
    new "The spirit twisted through the air a moment longer, before finally answering."

    old "This house is accommodating to your desires."
    new "This house is accommodating to your desires."

    old "Should you find yourself in need of a thing, all you must do is will it sufficiently and truthfully, and it will deliver."
    new "Should you find yourself in need of a thing, all you must do is will it sufficiently and truthfully, and it will deliver."

    old "For a moment, Sarah was happy to hear the answer and prepared to turn and leave, only for to realize the insanity of it."
    new "For a moment, Sarah was happy to hear the answer and prepared to turn and leave, only for to realize the insanity of it."

    old "She turned back towards Razaphel."
    new "She turned back towards Razaphel."

    old "You...you say the house gives me what I want?"
    new "You...you say the house gives me what I want?"

    old "Yes, to an extent."
    new "Yes, to an extent."

    old "Surely this cannot surprise you too much, you have known the house to shift and alter itself."
    new "Surely this cannot surprise you too much, you have known the house to shift and alter itself."

    old "To be larger within than without."
    new "To be larger within than without."

    old "I knew it wasn't a normal house, I figured that out years ago...but I figured it was just...magic."
    new "I knew it wasn't a normal house, I figured that out years ago...but I figured it was just...magic."

    old "That it was Xan who was doing it."
    new "That it was Xan who was doing it."

    old "The spirit flinched at the mention of the mage's name."
    new "The spirit flinched at the mention of the mage's name."

    old "No. The house moved to the mage's will, but it was not his doing."
    new "No. The house moved to the mage's will, but it was not his doing."

    old "Sarah frowned her brow, trying to make sense of it."
    new "Sarah frowned her brow, trying to make sense of it."

    old "What then? What is this house, exactly?"
    new "What then? What is this house, exactly?"

    old "Razaphel spun and brought its face-mask close to Sarah's face."
    new "Razaphel spun and brought its face-mask close to Sarah's face."

    old "Its inscrutable features made it hard to ever know what the spirit was truly thinking."
    new "Its inscrutable features made it hard to ever know what the spirit was truly thinking."

    old "Are you familiar with a river-rock-crab?"
    new "Are you familiar with a river-rock-crab?"

    old "Sarah was surprised to hear those words coming from the spirit."
    new "Sarah was surprised to hear those words coming from the spirit."

    old "I...of course I am. I'm from Rosanna, they're everywhere. You can find them in just about every river."
    new "I...of course I am. I'm from Rosanna, they're everywhere. You can find them in just about every river."

    old "And can you tell me...why they are called as such?"
    new "And can you tell me...why they are called as such?"

    old "Well...their shell is grey, like the pebbels founds by the side of the river. So they kind of look like rocks."
    new "Well...their shell is grey, like the pebbels founds by the side of the river. So they kind of look like rocks."

    old "The spirit's body slowly twisted and floated through the hall, turning thin as mist."
    new "The spirit's body slowly twisted and floated through the hall, turning thin as mist."

    old "Yes, that is correct."
    new "Yes, that is correct."

    old "Now tell me this. Is a river-rock-crab a crab, or a rock?"
    new "Now tell me this. Is a river-rock-crab a crab, or a rock?"

    old "Sarah was confused at the question, but decided to play along."
    new "Sarah was confused at the question, but decided to play along."

    old "It's a crab, obviously."
    new "It's a crab, obviously."

    old "Correct."
    new "Correct."

    old "But tell me, why is it not a rock?"
    new "But tell me, why is it not a rock?"

    old "Again, Sarah was confused, but she continued."
    new "Again, Sarah was confused, but she continued."

    old "Just because it looks like a rock, doesn't mean it is a rock. It's basic camouflage."
    new "Just because it looks like a rock, doesn't mean it is a rock. It's basic camouflage."

    old "And there you have your answer."
    new "And there you have your answer."

    old "Sarah looked confused at the spirit and considered his words."
    new "Sarah looked confused at the spirit and considered his words."

    old "Then, they struck her like lightining."
    new "Then, they struck her like lightining."

    old "A...a...are you suggesting...this house..."
    new "A...a...are you suggesting...this house..."

    old "Is not a house."
    new "Is not a house."

    old "It looks like one, but it is not a house. Not really."
    new "It looks like one, but it is not a house. Not really."

    old "In fact, it is quite similar to the river-rock-crabs, but perhaps only its methods are more...advanced."
    new "In fact, it is quite similar to the river-rock-crabs, but perhaps only its methods are more...advanced."

    old "Sarah suddenly felt her body shiver, the whole of the house..."
    new "Sarah suddenly felt her body shiver, the whole of the house..."

    old "So you're saying we're..."
    new "So you're saying we're..."

    old "Standing in the insides of a creature?"
    new "Standing in the insides of a creature?"

    old "The thought alone was enough to strike terror in her."
    new "The thought alone was enough to strike terror in her."

    old "No...that's impossible!"
    new "No...that's impossible!"

    old "There is no creature in the world that can do something like this."
    new "There is no creature in the world that can do something like this."

    old "That is true, but this particular creature is not from your world or mine. Some other place altogether."
    new "That is true, but this particular creature is not from your world or mine. Some other place altogether."

    old "I do not know. Even I do not hold all the answers."
    new "I do not know. Even I do not hold all the answers."

    old "All I know is that by some unfortunate circumstance, centuries by now, this creature found itself trapped in our reality."
    new "All I know is that by some unfortunate circumstance, centuries by now, this creature found itself trapped in our reality."

    old "Exposed to a hostile world, it did what most animals would do. It hid itself."
    new "Exposed to a hostile world, it did what most animals would do. It hid itself."

    old "Sarah stared at every part of the building, suddenly horrified at it."
    new "Sarah stared at every part of the building, suddenly horrified at it."

    old "How did it come to be here?"
    new "How did it come to be here?"

    old "I believe in time it was discovered by the mage order, more observant than most ordinary people."
    new "I believe in time it was discovered by the mage order, more observant than most ordinary people."

    old "They found the creature, and fearing for its life still, it threw itself on their mercy."
    new "They found the creature, and fearing for its life still, it threw itself on their mercy."

    old "And as you might imagine, the creature was happy to serve its new masters if it meant its survival."
    new "And as you might imagine, the creature was happy to serve its new masters if it meant its survival."

    old "And Xan was his master?"
    new "And Xan was his master?"

    old "He was the most powerful thing in this house, and so the creature bend itself to his mercy."
    new "He was the most powerful thing in this house, and so the creature bend itself to his mercy."

    old "For a moment the spirit paused."
    new "For a moment the spirit paused."

    old "But, with that mage gone, I suspect that his favor now falls on you."
    new "But, with that mage gone, I suspect that his favor now falls on you."

    old "Sarah looked at Razaphel, stunned."
    new "Sarah looked at Razaphel, stunned."

    old "You mean...it's afraid of me?"
    new "You mean...it's afraid of me?"

    old "Afraid. Or perhaps merely playing on your good nature."
    new "Afraid. Or perhaps merely playing on your good nature."

    old "I suspect that is also why you suddenly were able to find Xan's private study."
    new "I suspect that is also why you suddenly were able to find Xan's private study."

    old "Before, the house hid the room because its master did not want you to find it."
    new "Before, the house hid the room because its master did not want you to find it."

    old "Then, after the mage was gone, the house knew you were searching for something, and it offered it to you."
    new "Then, after the mage was gone, the house knew you were searching for something, and it offered it to you."

    old "Sarah felt the stress grow in her body."
    new "Sarah felt the stress grow in her body."

    old "But I never said I was looking for that room."
    new "But I never said I was looking for that room."

    old "No, but wherever this creature is from, the barriers of thoughts are not as...seperate as in your world or mine."
    new "No, but wherever this creature is from, the barriers of thoughts are not as...seperate as in your world or mine."

    old "Sarah looked around frantically for any sight of the creature, but found only the house."
    new "Sarah looked around frantically for any sight of the creature, but found only the house."

    old "You mean it can read my mind?"
    new "You mean it can read my mind?"

    old "Not quite so direct, I suspect. I believe instead he merely feels your mind. Feels your intentions."
    new "Not quite so direct, I suspect. I believe instead he merely feels your mind. Feels your intentions."

    old "And in turn, he proceeds you, delivers that which it knows you seek. Like a cat, delivering a mouse to its master."
    new "And in turn, he proceeds you, delivers that which it knows you seek. Like a cat, delivering a mouse to its master."

    old "Unbelievable..."
    new "Unbelievable..."

    old "Sarah was quite for a while as she considered."
    new "Sarah was quite for a while as she considered."

    old "It was a horrifying thought, that this house was in fact a living thing, but at the same time, the more she thought, the more it appeared to her as a powerful ally."
    new "It was a horrifying thought, that this house was in fact a living thing, but at the same time, the more she thought, the more it appeared to her as a powerful ally."

    old "Can I trust it? The house?"
    new "Can I trust it? The house?"

    old "You can trust it to do what it has done for centuries. Survive."
    new "You can trust it to do what it has done for centuries. Survive."

    old "If you give it what it wants, it will return the favor. It possess few desires outside of that base instinct, from what I have been able to deduce."
    new "If you give it what it wants, it will return the favor. It possess few desires outside of that base instinct, from what I have been able to deduce."

    old "Fine...I think I understand then."
    new "Fine...I think I understand then."

    old "Very well, then I shall part ways with you. Other affairs to see to."
    new "Very well, then I shall part ways with you. Other affairs to see to."

    old "You have other affairs?"
    new "You have other affairs?"

    old "Maybe I'm going to look for new friends, as my old friends have advised me."
    new "Maybe I'm going to look for new friends, as my old friends have advised me."

    old "Just like that, the spirit faded away."
    new "Just like that, the spirit faded away."

    old "Sarah doubted she would ever manage to get the spirit to stop being obtuse."
    new "Sarah doubted she would ever manage to get the spirit to stop being obtuse."

    old "Slowly, she turned and began to make her way down the hall."
    new "Slowly, she turned and began to make her way down the hall."

    old "With the new knowledge that she had gained from Razaphel, regarding the nature of the house, it now appeared very different to Sarah."
    new "With the new knowledge that she had gained from Razaphel, regarding the nature of the house, it now appeared very different to Sarah."

    old "Each step, a creaking of the floorboard. Sarah hoped the house would take no offense."
    new "Each step, a creaking of the floorboard. Sarah hoped the house would take no offense."

    old "Sorry...house..."
    new "Sorry...house..."

    old "Is that what I call you?"
    new "Is that what I call you?"

    old "Other than the echo of her own voice, there came no reponse."
    new "Other than the echo of her own voice, there came no reponse."

    old "Talking to a house, that's what my life has become, Sarah thought as he continued to make her way."
    new "Talking to a house, that's what my life has become, Sarah thought as he continued to make her way."

    old "Sarah shook her head and forced herself to clear it."
    new "Sarah shook her head and forced herself to clear it."

    old "Focus, she thought."
    new "Focus, she thought."

    old "Something to distract her."
    new "Something to distract her."

    old "She walked down the hall, trying door after door, finding only familar rooms."
    new "She walked down the hall, trying door after door, finding only familar rooms."

    old "For nearly an hour, Sarah walked and searched the house, growing increasingly desperate."
    new "For nearly an hour, Sarah walked and searched the house, growing increasingly desperate."

    old "She was all but ready to give up when her eye fell on a door."
    new "She was all but ready to give up when her eye fell on a door."

    old "A new door."
    new "A new door."

    old "Hesitantly, she approached it and reached out to touch the handle, still shiny and new."
    new "Hesitantly, she approached it and reached out to touch the handle, still shiny and new."

    old "With surprising ease, the door flew open."
    new "With surprising ease, the door flew open."

    old "Rushing forward to meet her was a gust of warm and humid air."
    new "Rushing forward to meet her was a gust of warm and humid air."

    old "Sarah stepped forward, through the opening."
    new "Sarah stepped forward, through the opening."

    old "For a moment, Sarah could see but her mind could make no sense of it."
    new "For a moment, Sarah could see but her mind could make no sense of it."

    old "A bubble of sensations of touch, smell, sight, each overpowering her senses."
    new "A bubble of sensations of touch, smell, sight, each overpowering her senses."

    old "Only slowly could she piece together where she was standing."
    new "Only slowly could she piece together where she was standing."

    old "A bathhouse."
    new "A bathhouse."

    old "In the middle of the house, there now appeared to exist a complete and furnished bathhouse."
    new "In the middle of the house, there now appeared to exist a complete and furnished bathhouse."

    old "No, Sarah realized as her eyes explored the room."
    new "No, Sarah realized as her eyes explored the room."

    old "It didn't just exist, it seemed to have existed here all this time. Present, obvious, logical. As if it belonged here."
    new "It didn't just exist, it seemed to have existed here all this time. Present, obvious, logical. As if it belonged here."

    old "Steam rising up from the surface of the water clogged up the air, making it hard to see all across the room."
    new "Steam rising up from the surface of the water clogged up the air, making it hard to see all across the room."

    old "Sarah could feel the mist condensate onto her skin, turning into beads of water and trickling down her face."
    new "Sarah could feel the mist condensate onto her skin, turning into beads of water and trickling down her face."

    old "The smell of the room, an odd mix of fruits and herbs, present but now overwhelming, oddly soothing to her mind."
    new "The smell of the room, an odd mix of fruits and herbs, present but now overwhelming, oddly soothing to her mind."

    old "Sarah felt her eyes slowly drawn to the water of the room."
    new "Sarah felt her eyes slowly drawn to the water of the room."

    old "A soft ripple ran across the surface, a current of some kind."
    new "A soft ripple ran across the surface, a current of some kind."

    old "Clear and blue, it was above all inviting to her."
    new "Clear and blue, it was above all inviting to her."

    old "Every part of her wanted to jump in."
    new "Every part of her wanted to jump in."

    old "And no sooner had the thought come to her, then Sarah realized that there wasn't anything stopping her."
    new "And no sooner had the thought come to her, then Sarah realized that there wasn't anything stopping her."

    old "Suddenly breaking from the trance, Sarah remembered Samayra, likely patiently waiting."
    new "Suddenly breaking from the trance, Sarah remembered Samayra, likely patiently waiting."

    old "Sarah turned back to the door to the room and called out to the girl."
    new "Sarah turned back to the door to the room and called out to the girl."

    old "Her voice echoed."
    new "Her voice echoed."

    old "Louder, a second time, Sarah now heard footsteps rushing up the hallway."
    new "Louder, a second time, Sarah now heard footsteps rushing up the hallway."

    old "It wasn't long before she saw the animated face of the former princess."
    new "It wasn't long before she saw the animated face of the former princess."

    old "Sarah! What is it?"
    new "Sarah! What is it?"

    old "The girl had barely finished her sentence when she stepped into the room and she was struck mute."
    new "The girl had barely finished her sentence when she stepped into the room and she was struck mute."

    old "Wooooow..."
    new "Wooooow..."

    old "Her voice echoed out."
    new "Her voice echoed out."

    old "Yeah...it's quite something, isn't it?"
    new "Yeah...it's quite something, isn't it?"

    old "The girl quickly spun around to her."
    new "The girl quickly spun around to her."

    old "Can we use it?"
    new "Can we use it?"

    old "Sarah could see a wide smile on Samayra's face. The girl was genuinely happy."
    new "Sarah could see a wide smile on Samayra's face. The girl was genuinely happy."

    old "Sure, why not. It's ours...I think."
    new "Sure, why not. It's ours...I think."

    old "Eager to feel the water on her skin, Sarah began to strip."
    new "Eager to feel the water on her skin, Sarah began to strip."

    old "Sarah struggled to get rid of the first pieces."
    new "Sarah struggled to get rid of the first pieces."

    old "But as each piece came off, the next one seemed easier and easier, and before long, she felt herself pulling away the last of her clothes."
    new "But as each piece came off, the next one seemed easier and easier, and before long, she felt herself pulling away the last of her clothes."

    old "Sarah casually threw them off to her side on the ground, uncaring for where they might land."
    new "Sarah casually threw them off to her side on the ground, uncaring for where they might land."

    old "When the last of her clothes were gone, Sarah could feel the steam of the room run across her skin."
    new "When the last of her clothes were gone, Sarah could feel the steam of the room run across her skin."

    old "More than simply warm her, the mixture of water and herbs seemed almost healing to her."
    new "More than simply warm her, the mixture of water and herbs seemed almost healing to her."

    old "Sarah could feel the stress flow from her body. Bruises and pains seemed to simply vanish."
    new "Sarah could feel the stress flow from her body. Bruises and pains seemed to simply vanish."

    old "The water."
    new "The water."

    old "It had an almost magnetic pull on her."
    new "It had an almost magnetic pull on her."

    old "She wanted to feel it on her body, really feel it."
    new "She wanted to feel it on her body, really feel it."

    old "Breaking into large strides, Sarah ran forward, the steam rushing past her body as she moved faster and faster."
    new "Breaking into large strides, Sarah ran forward, the steam rushing past her body as she moved faster and faster."

    old "Then, right near the edge, she leapt."
    new "Then, right near the edge, she leapt."

    old "Wooo!"
    new "Wooo!"

    old "Sarah cried out as for a moment she soared through the air."
    new "Sarah cried out as for a moment she soared through the air."

    old "And then she crashed into the water."
    new "And then she crashed into the water."

    old "Exploding around her she could feel it rush up across her body and past her head, weaving in and around her hair and all over her body."
    new "Exploding around her she could feel it rush up across her body and past her head, weaving in and around her hair and all over her body."

    old "She opened her eyes under water and for a moment, observed the perfect world that existed underneath it."
    new "She opened her eyes under water and for a moment, observed the perfect world that existed underneath it."

    old "This easy, comfortable place."
    new "This easy, comfortable place."

    old "As she felt her breath run out, Sarah planted her feet on the floor of the spa and launched herself up."
    new "As she felt her breath run out, Sarah planted her feet on the floor of the spa and launched herself up."

    old "Breaking through the surface of the water, Sarah threw her arms up as if she reached for the ceiling."
    new "Breaking through the surface of the water, Sarah threw her arms up as if she reached for the ceiling."

    old "She fell back into the water and floated, weightlessly."
    new "She fell back into the water and floated, weightlessly."

    old "Sarah looked out to the doorway and saw Samayra still standing there, with simultaneously eagerness and trepidation."
    new "Sarah looked out to the doorway and saw Samayra still standing there, with simultaneously eagerness and trepidation."

    old "Get in here Samayra! The water is amazing!"
    new "Get in here Samayra! The water is amazing!"

    old "Hearing her voice seemed to break Samayra's trance."
    new "Hearing her voice seemed to break Samayra's trance."

    old "In less than a minute, her clothes came off and she leapt into the water."
    new "In less than a minute, her clothes came off and she leapt into the water."

    old "Sarah felt the water rush up to her from where Samayra had jumped in."
    new "Sarah felt the water rush up to her from where Samayra had jumped in."

    old "After a short moment, she saw Samayra's head pop out from beneath the surface."
    new "After a short moment, she saw Samayra's head pop out from beneath the surface."

    old "Her long black hair now wet, was draped across her face like a ghost."
    new "Her long black hair now wet, was draped across her face like a ghost."

    old "You always look so put together, but now..."
    new "You always look so put together, but now..."

    old "Don't be mean!"
    new "Don't be mean!"

    old "I'm sorry. You look great."
    new "I'm sorry. You look great."

    old "Samayra looked around the room as she began to slowly swim, almost float, through the water."
    new "Samayra looked around the room as she began to slowly swim, almost float, through the water."

    old "Back in Bagrad the palace had a place like this too..."
    new "Back in Bagrad the palace had a place like this too..."

    old "But whenever I had to take a bath, there would be servants around to help me."
